Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Halve, core, and thinly slice
@long green pepper{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, half
the @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), half the cilantro,
@sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{} until
thoroughly combined.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add green pepper and cook until slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground turkey{10%ounce} and season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}; cook until everything is coated and
glaze has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

> Simply cook through this step as instructed, swapping in turkey for pork.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with pork mixture
and slaw (draining first). Top with Sriracha mayo, @crispy fried onions{1},
and remaining cilantro. Serve.